  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\n> `expectSafeMemory` should be used when the developer wants to assert the memory safety of code within the given context, and it can be called multiple times in order to register several ranges that are okay to be touched.\r\n>>  So this would be in the test contract itself, e.g. if I'm testing library methods, and once called it applies to the rest of my test?\r\n>> > agree- Maybe we can add a configuration value in the `foundry.toml` to disable this range? Down to do this in a separate PR.\r\n\r\nFrom https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/4491\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
